cs.ET, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper focuses on the entanglement routing problem in quantum networks, which involves building long-distance entanglements for concurrent source-destination pairs through multiple hops. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which includes research on quantum computing and communication. The paper also discusses the unique properties of quantum networks, which suggests that it may fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes new routing algorithms, which could place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.PL (Programming Languages).
